Vice President Kamala Harris spoke with President Bola Tinubu of Nigeria, recognizing Nigeria as a global voice and Africa's largest democracy and economy. They expressed their commitment to defending democracy in West Africa and the Sahel and condemned the attempted takeover in Niger. The Vice President supported President Tinubu's economic reforms and discussed increasing private sector investment, digital inclusion, women's empowerment, and clean energy access. She emphasized the US government's support for Nigeria's democracy and good governance. They also highlighted the strong ties between the US and Nigeria, including people-to-people connections and the Diaspora.